<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1836,2043]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1437,153,791]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1836,1863]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body oval, convex, covered with whitish, suberect setae. Body brown, legs, antennae and mouthparts yellowish. Head very broad, 1.8× wider than width of interocular space, with fine punctation, punctures small, granulate, separated by a 2.0–3.0× diameter of a puncture, eyes moderately large, not protuberant. Pronotum transverse, widest at its base. Disc of pronotum with fine, granulate punctation, punctures separated by ca. 2.0× diameter of a puncture. Posterior margin of pronotum subtly bisinuate. Anterior angles protruding anteriorly, subtriangular, posterior angles obtuse. Scutellar shield subtriangular, covered with subtle punctation. Elytra oblong (left elytron missing in the studied specimen), without traces of longitudinal ridges, widest in the middle of their length, sides curved, regularly converging to apex in posterior 1/3. Humeri well marked. Punctation stronger than on pronotum, punctures elongate, distance between punctures ca. the diameter of a puncture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Male genitalia. Penis (L 
<quantity box="[476,579,261,287]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[590,673,261,287]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" precision="555" value="-0.09">
W 
<quantity box="[624,673,261,287]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09</quantity>
</geoCoordinate>
mm, 
<figureCitation box="[738,840,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1766,1791]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,971,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,971,1727]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 24. Calvariopsis nana sp. nov., male. A) penis; B) tergite VIII; C) tergite IX. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2783786/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
) with curved sides, parameroids short, subtriangular, trigonium subtriangular. Tegmen and sternite IX missing in the studied specimen. Tergite VIII (L 
<quantity box="[1241,1343,297,323]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.26">0.26 mm</quantity>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1354,1436,297,323]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" precision="555" value="-0.24">
W 
<quantity box="[1387,1436,297,323]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.24">0.24</quantity>
</geoCoordinate>
mm, 
<figureCitation box="[209,308,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1766,1791]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,971,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,971,1727]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 24. Calvariopsis nana sp. nov., male. A) penis; B) tergite VIII; C) tergite IX. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2783786/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
) with shallow V-shaped emargination of apical margin, two sharp denticles in lateral portions of apical plate and short setae on posterolateral portion, apodemes as long as apical plate, slightly diverging. Tergite IX (L 
<quantity box="[151,253,405,431]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23 mm</quantity>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[265,347,405,431]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" precision="555" value="-0.19">
W 
<quantity box="[298,347,405,431]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.19">0.19</quantity>
</geoCoordinate>
mm, 
<figureCitation box="[412,512,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1766,1791]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,971,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,971,1727]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 24. Calvariopsis nana sp. nov., male. A) penis; B) tergite VIII; C) tergite IX. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2783786/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 24C</figureCitation>
) with membranous apical plate, apical margin covered with short setae, apodemes as long as apical plate, diverging.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,153,791]" box="[199,414,477,503]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
